h2. Supported Gecode features 

Note that, while Gecode/R uses Gecode 1.3.1, the following links point to the
Gecode 2.0 documentation. Hence the linked documentation does not correctly 
reflect the constraints supported. In most cases the difference is small. Refer 
to the corresponding Gecode 1.3.1 documentation for a more accurate view.

* Boolean variables with the following constraints
** "Simple relation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntRelBool.html
** "Linear":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntLinearBool.html
* Finite domain integer variables with the following constraints
** "Arithmetic":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntArith.html
** "Cardinality":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntCard.html without global cardinality constraints
** "Channel":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntChannel.html
** "Distinct":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntDistinct.html
** "Domain":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntDomain.html
** "Element":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntElement.html
** "Linear":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntLinearInt.html
** "Simple relation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntRelInt.html
** "Sorting":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntSorted.html
* Finite integer sets with the following constraints
** Distinct
** "Domain":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetDom.html
** "Connection constraints to finite domain variables":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetConnect.html
** "Relation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetRel.html
** "Set selection":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetSelection.html
** "Set operation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetRelOp.html
* Branching selection
* Depth first search
* Reification and propagation strength
* Branch and bound search

h2. Features not supported

The following are some notable features that are included in Gecode but _not_
in Gecode/R (but might be in the future). Note that the list is based on the
Gecode 1.3.1 feature set.

* Unsupported integer constraints
** Regular
** "Global cardinality":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntCard.html
** "Scheduling":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelIntScheduling.html
* Unsupported set constraints
** "Convexity":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetConvex.html
** "Sequence":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetSequence.html
** "Projector":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-latest/group__TaskModelSetProjector.html
* Limited discrepancy search
* Custom propagators and branching strategies
